Program: Discovery
Title: Genes - the shape of things to come
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrxks
Last Broadcast Date: 09 January 2000
A look at the pattern of gene formation in humans. How does a single cell become a human being? The programme looks how genes make sure we end up the way we do. Using the hox gene found by researching the fruit fly has shed light on the process of evolution.